  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dad\u0dca \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If the price of oil goes down, the price of food will also go down",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Asela Sampath, President of the Restaurant Owners Association, said in a press conference held in Elpitiya that if the price of fuel is reduced, the price of food and beverages in restaurants will be reduced by twenty percent and because gas supply is being done very actively, most of the restaurants that were closed have now been opened.",
        "Mr. Asela also said that if the price of fuel decreases significantly, he will reduce the price of food in his restaurants by twenty percent. Accordingly, Mr. Asela further added that the price of rice and rice will also decrease from plenty."
      ],
